            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Your HVAC technician needs unobstructed access to both indoor components (typically in closet, garage, or attic) and outdoor condenser unit to perform thorough diagnosis and service. For indoor units, remove any stored items, boxes, clothing, or household goods stacked around or in front of the air handler, furnace, or closet housing HVAC equipment. Many Picture Rocks homes use garage-mounted air handlers—clear a 3-foot workspace around the unit and ensure safe access to attic equipment if applicable. For outdoor condenser units common on desert properties, clear away any tumbleweeds, dead vegetation, debris, pet toys, or equipment stored within 3-4 feet of the unit. Picture Rocks properties often accumulate windblown debris during monsoon season—spending a few minutes clearing the area prevents delays and allows technicians to safely assess your system. If you have dogs or other pets, please secure them in a separate area before the technician arrives. Many Picture Rocks properties have dogs that patrol the yard—even friendly dogs can complicate outdoor unit service and create safety concerns."
